We had a lovely dining experience the evening of 1/23/21.  We were seated promptly with our reservation, and I liked the attention to covid rules. My wife ordered a split of Maschio Prosecco and I ordered a glass of Antinori Pepoli Chianti.  Troy, our server, was attentive without pretension, was energetic, and had answers to all our questions.  His assistant, who seemed to bus and attend every filled table, was equally but delightfully capable. My wife ordered the minestrone, which she still  believes to be the best in the city, and I ordered the stuffed mushrooms.  The vegetables added individual as well as total flavor without covering the crab flavor of the stuffing.  Troy brought over some hot cylinder rolls, covered in seasoned parmesan, which served well to sop up the stuffing sauce. For entrees she ordered the spaghetti and meatballs; and I, my favorite dish here, the Frutti Di Mare.  The angel hair and rich marina was served on the side, and Fausto has an exception version.  The main dish was pure seafood: fish, calamari, shrimp, oysters, mussels, and clams in a light reduction sauce.  It is still my favorite. We took home about half the entrees, and passed on dessert.  We were there maybe an hour to hour and a quarter.  It was a fine experience and recommend it without question if you are into local Italian cuisine.
